race.comment: PRETTY PLEASE (1) has raced well at all three runs this prep on her home track of Kembla, most recently on Saturday when she chimed in late on to miss by a whisker over today's trip. Only needs to hold that form to be taking this out. TSARINA DIAMONDS (3) is the best hope of causing an upset. Good effort two back when beaten a long neck as favourite in a Class 1 over the mile at Canberra. Will race on the speed with winkers on for the first time and should take some catching. BURNING AMBITION (2) ran a better race last time out when he closed well to grab second over 1675m at Wagga Riverside. Not out of the contest based on that performance. BASTION (4) has raced just twice and lacked the turn of foot required in shorter races. Might come into his own with this step up in journey. KINDAMAGIC (7) worked home well when resuming Goulburn last start and an extra 400m is to her advantage.
